<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911119-0017</DOCNO><DOCID>911119-0017.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Rollins Environmental Services:   Fire Caused Some Damage   Sunday at a Texas Facility</HL><DATE>11/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   REN</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>POLLUTION CONTROL, WASTE MANAGEMENT SERVICES (POL)INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL SERVICES (SVC)</IN><RE>DELAWARE (DE)NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Rollins Environmental Services Inc., Wilmington, Del.,said a fire occurred on Sunday during a severe thunder andlightning storm at its facility in Deer Park, Texas.   The commercial incineration company, which operates in thechemical waste treatment and disposal industry, said the firewas caused by elevated temperatures in the fiberglass-linedair pollution control equipment. An official said the companyis investigating why the sensors that detect highertemperatures didn't pick up the temperature rise.</LP><TEXT>   There weren't any injuries or harm to the environment, thecompany said. The fire, limited to the air pollution controlequipment, was brought under control and extinguished inabout two hours.   Early estimates are for repairs to take at least fourweeks before operations are restored to normal. The companysaid it is insured for both property damage and businessinterruption, but it couldn't yet estimate the damage.</TEXT></DOC>